[![Las Canteras beach in Las Palmas de Gran Canaria. Foto by Bengt Nyman.](photos/canteras.jpeg)](https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/1/1e/Playa_de_las_Canteras_2016_33.jpg)

Welcome to the **Canteras Microbiome Project**! A research project of marine microbial indicators of biological contamination in Las Palmas de Gran Canaria, Spain. This project is made in association with [Biological Oceanography in a Changing Ocean - IOCAG](https://www.gob-iocag.ulpgc.es/) and their team from the University of Las Palmas de Gran Canaria.

## The Monitoring Program

The microbiome monitoring consists of 47 samples collected at 5 locations across Las Canteras and El Confital. The monitoring of environmental parameters including cytometry compromised a larger frame, with 8 locations (@fig-map). Microbiome monitoring spanned for 2 years, it began in July 2021 and ended in April 2023, with a sampling frequency of around 1 month. Environmental parameters began their sampling in April 2020, coinciding with lock down of economic activity due to the COVID-19 pandemic (@fig-samples).

